             On Wednesday, March 19 as part of the �Community Champions Week� for the �March For Meals� campaign, New Providence Police Chief Anthony Buccelli, Springfield Police Chief John Cook and Summit Police Chief Robert Weck participated by delivering meals to seniors in their respective communities.  SAGE Eldercare in Summit coordinates meal deliveries to older adults in parts of Union, Essex and Morris Counties through Meals On Wheels Association of America.  For more information on the program, call 908.273.5554 or visit <a href="http://www.sageeldercare.org" target="_blank">www.sageeldercare.org</a>.
